<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="51" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,386,699]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,386,411]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The species is distinguishable from other species of the genus by the forewing dark red oblique triangular patch from base to apex on the forewing. In the female genitalia, the ductus bursae appears as long as the corpus bursae, while the ductus bursae is much shorter than corpus bursae in 
<taxonomicName box="[1015,1134,459,483]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Micardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallens" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1015,1134,459,483]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">M. pallens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1140,1227,459,482]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
